			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>
<DIV><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>Doppleganger - shorten reuse timer <FONT color=#ff0000>DONE, shortened to 30 minutes</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>
<DIV><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? 10pt; **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>There has been no further update at this time regarding any of the old issues on your class list.&nbsp; I have altered the list to reflect the new items added and submitted.</SPAN></DIV></SPAN></SPAN>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reduce npc immunity to spells such as mez, charm, stun and pacify</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>(partially implemented)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Improvement to Tash line – reduction in agro and larger MR debuff</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time) </FONT><FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>The biggest concern is the amount of aggro Tash generates compared to the Shaman debuff spell </SPAN><namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><place><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>Melos</SPAN></place><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> that debuffs more stats.&nbsp; Making Innoruuk's Sarcasm augments more available (LDoN vender or questable)&nbsp;would be a good first step to&nbsp;fix this issue.&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>A way to upgrade the MR debuff without making it unbalancing is to add a 2nd component that does not stack with the Shaman/Mage debuff line.&nbsp; Have one part that debuffs the normal 50 MR, then a 2nd part that debuffs another 20-30 MR.&nbsp; If Malos/Malosinia gets casted on the mob then the 2nd part gets overwriten but the 1st part remains.</SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Add resist adj to bliss/apathy of the nihil</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Doppelganger – drop all agro</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time) <FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT>, </FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>shorten reuse timer</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><STRONG>DONE</STRONG> now 30 minutes</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>Upon the death of a Doppelganger the Enchanter should be cleared from that mobs hate list because that mob will now think that the Enchanter is dead.&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>Another problem is after hitting the Doppelganger hotkey the Enchanter will sometimes die anyway.&nbsp; This is due to low health aggro.&nbsp; A small heal taking the enchanter upto 40% health needs to be added to this skill to fix the low health aggro death issue.&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>Lowering the reuse timer to 30 minutes was a good start.&nbsp; But many Enchanters want it to be lower.&nbsp; Also there is not a big advantage to getting over level 1 of Doppelganger.&nbsp; A way to fix both issues is to shorten the reuse timer for the higher levels.&nbsp; Level one remains the same, level two lowers it to 20 minutes, and level 3 lowers the reuse timer to 10-15 minutes.</SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Increase utility of Mez Mastery</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time) </FONT><FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>Some Enchanters are concerned that Mez Mastery will have less utility in the future if there is no Word of Morell&nbsp;upgrade in OoW expansion.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>For 20 AA's perhaps have it also reduce resists on all mezzes, and have to give a faster cast time/recast time on mezzes.&nbsp;&nbsp; (Some enchanters would not mind a whole new set of AA's that give those benefits)</SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self only mana regen - stackable with other mana regen buffs</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Improve enchanter animation spell &amp; add higher level animation </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>(no planned change at this time) </FONT><FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>More HP so that&nbsp;the animation&nbsp;can survive getting hit a few times by green mobs.&nbsp; The enchanter animation has no chance of surviving more than&nbsp;one second of&nbsp;enrage from a GoD mob.&nbsp; (Not enough time to back him off)</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>"/Pet Hold" would be nice so Enchanters could use our pets on raids.&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Add "unable to be mezzed" message BEFORE the mez attempt</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>.</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;> <FONT color=#0000ff>(NEW)</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: COLOR: red;>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>This would save Enchanters many deaths when trying to mezz too high or Immune mobs.&nbsp;&nbsp;This addresses the issue of having mobs which are named the same, con the same, look the same, but some are mezzable and some are not.&nbsp; At present high end mezzing is a crap shoot and groups/raids solve it by off-tanking. Getting a resist is one thing<FONT color=#000000>, casting a spell when you have no idea if it will work of not is entirely another.</FONT></SPAN></P></SPAN>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: windowtext; COLOR:>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide a stacking mana regen advantage to grouping with enchanters.</SPAN><SPAN> <FONT color=#0000ff>(NEW)</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>Something like&nbsp;an AA or spell&nbsp;that gives the enchanters current group&nbsp;a rune and mana regen for 1 minute.&nbsp; With KEI having a long duration groups don't really need an enchanter in the group.&nbsp; They can just get KEI or even VoQ and go out to do an LDoN mission.&nbsp; This would give people yet another reason to add an enchanter to their group, even if they already have KEI (which they usually do).&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>A few classes seem to get a paragon-type spell,&nbsp;except&nbsp;enchanters who are supposed to be the mana regen (power of mind) class. Ours should not only provide nice regen, but a unique effect to compliment one of our abilities, namely rune. </SPAN></P>
<P tab-stops: justify; 5.75in? **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN:></SPAN><SPAN>10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reduce casting time on Forlorn Deeds to 3 seconds and add resists adjustment&nbsp;<FONT color=#0000ff>(NEW)</FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE:>This Kunark era spell needs an upgrade to fit todays content.&nbsp; 6 seconds is way to long for fighting GoD mobs that don't have many HP's.&nbsp; Beastlords who are a Hybrid class are now better slowers than Enchanters because of their faster casting slow that seems to resists less.</SPAN></P></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:>&nbsp;Ky</P></DIV>
