<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reduce npc immunity to spells such as mez, charm, stun and pacify </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(partially implemented)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Improvement to Tash line – reduction in agro and larger MR debuff </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time)</FONT> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: blue;><FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT> <FONT color=#ff0000>(NO UPDATE ON THIS AT THIS TIME)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>The biggest concern is the amount of aggro Tash generates compared to the Shaman debuff spell </SPAN><namespace prefix = st1 ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"><place><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:>Melos</SPAN></place><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:> that debuffs more stats.&nbsp; Making Innoruuk's Sarcasm augments more available (LDoN vender or questable)&nbsp;would be a good first step to&nbsp;fix this issue.&nbsp; </SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">A way to upgrade the MR debuff without making it unbalancing is to add a 2nd component that does not stack with the Shaman/Mage debuff line.&nbsp; Have one part that debuffs the normal 50 MR, then a 2nd part that debuffs another 20-30 MR.&nbsp; If Malos/Malosinia gets casted on the mob then the 2nd part gets overwriten but the 1st part remains.</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Add resist adj to bliss/apathy of the nihil </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Doppelganger – drop all agro </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time)</FONT> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: blue;><FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT> <FONT color=#ff0000>(NO UPDATE ON THIS AT THIS TIME)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>, </FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>shorten reuse timer </SPAN><FONT color=#ff0000><B><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: 9pt; COLOR: red; Verdana; 12.0pt? mso-bidi-font-size: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>DONE</SPAN></B><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:> now 30 minutes</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Upon the death of a Doppelganger the Enchanter should be cleared from that mobs hate list because that mob will now think that the Enchanter is dead.&nbsp; </FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Another problem is after hitting the Doppelganger hotkey the Enchanter will sometimes die anyway.&nbsp; This is due to low health aggro.&nbsp; A small heal taking the enchanter upto 40% health needs to be added to this skill to fix the low health aggro death issue.&nbsp; </FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Lowering the reuse timer to 30 minutes was a good start.&nbsp; But many Enchanters want it to be lower.&nbsp; Also there is not a big advantage to getting over level 1 of Doppelganger.&nbsp; A way to fix both issues is to shorten the reuse timer for the higher levels.&nbsp; Level one remains the same, level two lowers it to 20 minutes, and level 3 lowers the reuse timer to 10-15 minutes.</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Increase utility of Mez Mastery </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time)</FONT> </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: blue;><FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT> <FONT color=#ff0000>(NO UPDATE ON THIS AT THIS TIME)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Some Enchanters are concerned that Mez Mastery will have less utility in the future if there is no Word of Morell&nbsp;upgrade in OoW expansion.</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN #cccccc? **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">For 20 AA's perhaps have it also reduce resists on all mezzes, and have to give a faster cast time/recast time on mezzes.&nbsp;&nbsp; (Some enchanters would not mind a whole new set of AA's that give those benefits)</FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Self only mana regen - stackable with other mana regen buffs </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></P>
<P justify; tab-stops: **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN: 5.75in?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: windowtext;>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Improve enchanter animation spell &amp; add higher level animation&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time)</FONT><FONT color=#cccccc> </FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE: blue;><FONT color=#0000ff>(reconsider please)</FONT><FONT color=#cccccc> </FONT><FONT color=#ff0000>(NO UPDATE ON THIS AT THIS TIME)</FONT></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: red;>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;>More HP so that&nbsp;the animation&nbsp;can survive getting hit a few times by green mobs.&nbsp; The enchanter animation has no chance of surviving more than&nbsp;one second of&nbsp;enrage from a GoD mob.&nbsp; (Not enough time to back him off)</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;>"/Pet Hold" would be nice so Enchanters could use our pets on raids.&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P justify; tab-stops: **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN: 5.75in?></SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: windowtext;>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Add "unable to be mezzed" message BEFORE the mez attempt</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;>.</SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: red;> <FONT color=#0000ff><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: red;>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;>This would save Enchanters many deaths when trying to mezz too high or Immune mobs.&nbsp;&nbsp;This addresses the issue of having mobs which are named the same, con the same, look the same, but some are mezzable and some are not.&nbsp; At present high end mezzing is a crap shoot and groups/raids solve it by off-tanking. Getting a resist is one thing, casting a spell when you have no idea if it will work of not is entirely another.<FONT color=#000000></FONT></SPAN></P></SPAN>
<P justify; tab-stops: **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN: 5.75in?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: windowtext;>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Provide a stacking mana regen advantage to grouping with enchanters.</SPAN><SPAN> <FONT color=#0000ff><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(currently being evaluated)</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;>Something like&nbsp;an AA or spell&nbsp;that gives the enchanters current group&nbsp;a rune and mana regen for 1 minute.&nbsp; With KEI having a long duration groups don't really need an enchanter in the group.&nbsp; They can just get KEI or even VoQ and go out to do an LDoN mission.&nbsp; This would give people yet another reason to add an enchanter to their group, even if they already have KEI (which they usually do).&nbsp; </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;>A few classes seem to get a paragon-type spell,&nbsp;except&nbsp;enchanters who are supposed to be the mana regen (power of mind) class. Ours should not only provide nice regen, but a unique effect to compliment one of our abilities, namely rune. </SPAN></P>
<P justify; tab-stops: **SMURF**?TEXT-ALIGN: 5.75in?></SPAN><SPAN>10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Reduce casting time on Forlorn Deeds to 3 seconds and add resists adjustment&nbsp;<FONT color=#0000ff><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? 9pt; COLOR: red; **Oompa-Loompa**?FONT-SIZE:><FONT color=#ff0000>(no change planned at this time) - </FONT><FONT color=#0000ff>spells and AAs from older expansions will not necessarily be as effective in newer content.&nbsp; Instead new spells and AAs will be introduced, this may be upgraded in future expansions.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></P><SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in TEXT-ALIGN: 0pt; **SMURF**?MARGIN: justify?><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt;>This Kunark era spell needs an upgrade to fit todays content.&nbsp; 6 seconds is way to long for fighting GoD mobs that don't have many HP's.&nbsp; Beastlords who are a Hybrid class are now better slowers than Enchanters because of their faster casting slow that seems to resists less.</SPAN></P></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:></SPAN>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; .25in? 0pt list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 l0 mso-list:><SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:>Ky</SPAN></P></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
